<HEADLINE> India Welcomes U.N. Team, but Rules Out Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- India said Thursday that any
team from the United Nations is welcome to the country but it
ruled out any third party mediation to resolve bilateral issues
between India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to a special team sent by U.N. Secretary General Kofi
Annan to tour Bangladesh, Pakistan and Sri Lanka, sources from the
Ministry of External Affairs said here that U.N. officials are
always welcome to visit India and have discussions on global
issues including nuclear disarmament.
</P>
<P>
India "has reiterated on many occasions that there is no scope
for third party mediation of any nature whatsoever in respect of
India's relations with Pakistan," the sources said.
</P>
<P>
India-Pakistan issues including Kashmir are purely bilateral
and have to be resolved through bilateral dialogue only, he added.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
