<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Far East Bowling Championships, HK Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to host the 15th
Far East Tenpin Bowling Championships and hold the 24th Hong Kong
International Open Tenpin Bowling Championships, it was announced
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Far East championships are scheduled for June 26-July 5 and
it will be immediately followed by the seven-day Hong Kong Open.
</P>
<P>
The Far East championships consist of singles, doubles, trios,
five-person team, all-events and masters. Entered in the
championships will be teams from China, Macao, Chinese Taipei,
Guam, Japan, South Korea and host Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Open will serve as a qualifying tournament for
the following Hong Kong Masters Cup, set for July 13-14, which is
the third leg of the five-leg inaugural Asian Tour.
</P>
<P>
The top 14 Asian men and women bowlers from each Open Men and
Ladies event of the selected International Open will qualify for
the Masters Cup.
</P>
<P>
Each participant will earn Tour ranking points according to
their positions. The top 16 men and women bowlers from the Tour
ranking list at the end of the season will qualify for the Grand
Slam Finals slated for January 16-17 next year in Taipei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
