<HEADLINE> Greece, Armenia Agree to Develop All-Round Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The parliament presidents of Greece
and Armenia agreed during their talks Thursday to further
strengthen the all-round relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after their talks, Greek Parliament President
Apostolos Kaklamanis described Greek-Armenian ties as "at a very
high level," saying that both countries aimed to further such ties
in all sectors, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Khosrov Haroutunian, who is in Greece for a
visit, said that the strong relations between the two countries
could contribute to consolidating peace and stability in the
Caucasus and Black Sea region.
</P>
<P>
Both men said that they intended to increase cooperation
between the two parliaments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
