<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican, Netherlands Qualify after 2-2 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Mexico salvaged a 2-2 draw with
the Netherlands on Thursday and both teams qualified for the second
round.
</P>
<P>
The first half saw the domination of the Dutch team and just
five minutes into the match, Phillip Cocu put the Netherlands 1-0
ahead as he beat the Mexican defender and the charging out
goal-keeper with a right-footer.
</P>
<P>
Some 13 minutes later, Ronald De Boer picked the ball in the
Mexican area and slamed it home to give the Dutch a 2-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
It seemed that the Dutch could win the match easily but in the
second half, the Mexican refused to give up and quickened their pace.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands made some substitutions in the second half and lost
the domination of midfield. The Mexican team took full advantage of
that and forced the Dutch team into defence with quick attacking.
</P>
<P>
Their efforts paid off at the 75th minute when Ricardo Pelaez
jumped high and headed home to make it 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Mexico were disallowed a goal at the 89th minute as the referee
called it off-side. Ramon Ramirez argued the decision with the
referee and was shown the red card.
</P>
<P>
The sent-off didn't shake the Mexicans' determination and they
kept on attacking. Just seconds before the final whistle, Luis
Hernandez hit in the equaliser three meters in front of the goal to
complete the exciting game.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands and Mexican both have five points to their credit
and the Dutch team qualified as the group winners as they have a
better goal difference than the Mexican team.
</P>
<P>
In the other match played at the Parc des Princes stadium in
Paris, South Korea forced the Belgian team to a 1-1 draw.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans and the Belgian team were both eliminated.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
