<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-25 16:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting on Twinned Mediterranean Towns Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 230 administrative
officials of twinned towns from 10 Mediterranean countries are
gathering in Cyprus' western coastal town of Paphos Thursday to
promote cooperation and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference, its sixth in the region, will also on
the role local administration can play in enhancing cooperation
and development in Mediterranean countries in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The participants will give special emphasis on programs of the
European Union (EU), the role of twinned towns, possibilities and
prospects in the economic field and matters such as xenophobia,
racism and common cultural heritage.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides sent his opening statement
to the meeting, which said cooperation between Mediterranean local
administration institutions is a decisive factor for stability,
peace and prosperity in the region.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session, Greece's EU Commissioner,
Christos Papoutsis, stressed the need for Euro-Mediterranean
cooperation. He said the EU Commission is determined to reinforce
it in a bid to secure social and economic balance in the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
