<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Scuttles Belgium with 1-1 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A second-half equalizer from Yoo Sang
Chul doused Belgium's hope to qualify for the second round of the
World Cup finals here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 1-1 draw at Parc des Princes meant that Belgium failed to
qualify for the first time for the second round of the top soccer
competition since 1982.
</P>
<P>
Yoo, the veteran defender from Ulsan Hyundai, netted in the 72nd
minute on a pass from Ha Seok Ju.
</P>
<P>
The Koreans, playing only for pride as they had been eliminated
after their second group match, also had opportunities to win their
first game in five World Cup finals but Choi Yong Soo headed twice
over the crossbar within a span of three minutes.
</P>
<P>
PSV Eindhoven forward Luc Nilis gave Belgium a 1-0 lead before
break when he blasted the ball into the net in the seventh minute.
</P>
<P>
He scored by picking up a rebound off a Korean defender when Gordan
Vidovic tried to head the ball in.
</P>
<P>
Enzo Scifo had an earlier chance to score but the 20-meter shot was
saved by South Korean keeper Kim Byung Ji.
</P>
<P>
Belgium, who had had to win the game to enter the last sixteen,
finished the group E third behind second-placers Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, who tied with Mexico 2-2 in the other game on
Thursday, finished atop the group while South Korea was at bottom.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
