<HEADLINE> Arab League Criticizes Israel's Jerusalem Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) Thursday
strongly denounced an Israeli decision to expand Jerusalem as
having "adverse impact on the entire (Middle East) peace process,"
the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision will "give Israel full control of the holy city,
obliterate its Arab entity and change its demographic feature," a
statement issue at the end of an AL meeting said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli cabinet on Sunday approved a plan to set up an
"umbrella authority" for Jerusalem over eight West Bank Jewish
settlements to the east, south and north.
</P>
<P>
The 22-nation Arab organization urged the United Nations
Security Council to discuss the Israeli "dangerous decision."
</P>
<P>
It called the Israeli plan a flagrant violation of the relevant
United Nations resolutions, under which any Israeli measures
adopted for the holy city are null and void.
</P>
<P>
The AL voiced full support for the Palestinians, who have been
pinning the blame on Israel for changing the status of Jerusalem
by approving the plan.
</P>
<P>
Agreements signed between the Palestinians and Israel demand
that neither side take unilateral actions concerning the city,
which should be negotiated in the final status talks.
</P>
<P>
The AL called on the United States and Russia, co-sponsors of
the peace process, and the European Union to take serious and
decisive stances regarding Israel's activities, which it said
"disregard the rights and feelings of both Muslims and Christians
worldwide."
</P>
<P>
It called for intensive consultations to adopt a unified stance
that will help protect Arab rights and offer all possible support
to the Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
