<HEADLINE> 12 Die in Traffic Accident in N. Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A traffic accident in northern
Zambia has left 12 people dead on the spot while 21 others
injured after the truck they were traveling in tried to avoid
road drums and overturned.
</P>
<P>
Zambia News Agency ZANA Thursday quoted Starfor Phiri,
northwestern province police regional commanding officer, who
confirmed the accident as saying Thursday that the accident
happened around 21:00 hours Wednesday when the vehicle was going
to Zambezi from Solwezi.
</P>
<P>
The injured were later admitted to Solwezi general hospital
and now all of them are out of danger, according to the
hospital's executive director Sylvester Chilaika.
</P>
<P>
The driver, who survived the accident, said at the hospital
that the truck overturned because a construction company
currently tarring the road has not put up road deviation signs to
show that the main road is closed.
</P>
<P>
He said since he was driving at night, he realized too late
that the road has been closed and saw the drums barriers rather
too late and as he swayed trying to avoid hitting into the drums,
the vehicle overturned.
</P>
<P>
Over the weekend, another motorist also overturned at the same
spot around 24:00 hours, said ZANA. He blamed the construction
company for not putting up deviation signs to warn motorists for
the barrier ahead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
