<HEADLINE> U.S., Norway Aid Ethiopia in Health, Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A five-million-U.S. Dollar
grant agreement was signed here Thursday between the governments
of Ethiopia and the United States of America.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by Ethiopia's Ministry of Economic
Development and Cooperation said the purpose of the agreement is
to introduce an amendment to the health sector program agreement
signed earlier and authorize the release of the amount to be used
for the essential services for health in the Ethiopia program.
</P>
<P>
The essential services for health in Ethiopia is a
56.5-million- US Dollar bilateral program using both project and
budgetary assistance to support the Ethiopian government in its
health sector development efforts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a specific grant agreement amounting to 1.5 million
US Dollars for the provision of technical and financial support
to medium scale hydro-electric power projects was also signed
here Thursday between the governments of Ethiopia and Norway.
</P>
<P>
The grant will enable the undertaking of pre-feasibility
studies on Genale, Guder, Baro and Geba hydropower projects in
Ethiopia, according to the press release. 
</P>
