<HEADLINE> U.S. President Clinton's Schedule Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Following is the schedule of U.S.
President William Clinton in Xi'an Friday.
</P>
<P>
He will visit Xiahe Village in Lintong District of Xi'an City
tomorrow morning.
</P>
<P>
The village has a population of 1,323 and the per capita annual
income is 3,283 yuan (about 400 U.S. dollars). The villagers' main
sources of income are making and selling of arts and crafts,
transport service, grain growing and fruit cultivation.
</P>
<P>
After touring the village, the president will go to see the
life-size terro-cotta warriors about one kilometer away from the
village, which were unearthed in the Mausoleum of the first
emperor of the Qin Dynasty (221-207 BC) and are taken as the
"eighth wonder of the world."
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Governor Cheng Andong will accompany Clinton to see the
terro-cotta warriors.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow evening, President Clinton will leave for Beijing, the
Chinese capital, by his presidential plane at the end of his visit
in Xi'an. Beijing is the second leg of his nine-day visit to China
and he is scheduled to visit Shanghai, a coastal economic and
financial metropolis, and Guilin whose scenery ranks first in the
country, and Hong Kong which returned to China a year ago.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton and his official delegation arrived in Xi'an
early this evening. 
</P>
