of the 2002 World Cup finals with Japan.
</P>
<P>
"Our losses to Mexico and the Netherlands really demoralized our
players, but today's draw was a reward for the fans' support and would
help our hosting of the 2002 finals," said Kim after their 1-1 tie.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who replaced Cha Bum Kun after their 5-0 loss to the Dutches,
added, "Our players played today to their great potential. After
conceding the goal in the first half, we had plenty of time trying to
equalize."
</P>
<P>
