<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Ancient Capital Opens Gate of Friendship for Clinton (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Through the centuries-old city gate
of the ancient capital of Xi'an, U.S. President Bill Clinton
walked into China today.
</P>
<P>
The suspension bridge, used to thwart enemies in ancient times,
serenely spanned the banks of the city moat, while the heavy iron
gate has been lifted to greet the first incumbent American
president who has come to visit China in nearly a decade.
</P>
<P>
In a dark suit matched with a yellow tie, President Clinton
made his appearance outside Yongning Gate, Xi'an southern city
gate, at about eight p.m. local time (12:00 GMT).
</P>
<P>
On the open ground in front of the city wall, the
two-millennium-old Xi'an, amid the thundering of 60 huge drums and
the strains of Tang Dynasty music, welcomed the American president
in a grand ceremony imitating that for greeting distinguished
guests in the heydays of the dynasty more than a millennium ago.
</P>
<P>
A myriad of color bulbs lit the grand city wall that has
silently guarded Xi'an for six centuries, presenting a magnificent
view of a golden-rimmed stone wall beneath the night sky.
</P>
<P>
Walking on the red-carpeted passage toward the Gate, President
Clinton was greeted by enthusiastic well-wishers with kids extending
their hands towards him.
</P>
<P>
At the foot of the city wall, Xi'an Mayor Feng Xuchu presented
the smiling Clinton with a golden key to the city gate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
