<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Christian Converts Hit 10 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The number of Chinese Christian
(Protestant) converts has grown from slightly over 100 to over 10
million since the 1840 Opium War, according to Ye Xiaowen,
director of the State Bureau of Religious Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Ye attributed the rapid growth to the independent principles of
the Chinese Christian Church.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at today's press conference hosted by the State
Council Information Office, Ye said the principles of
self-administration, self-support and self-propagation have
enabled the Chinese Christian churches to integrate traditional
Chinese culture and lifestyles.
</P>
<P>
The rapid increase in the number of Christian converts and the
development of China's churches indicates that Chinese Christian
converts perform better in expounding Christian doctrines and
managing their churches better than the foreign missionaries in
the past, according to Ye.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Chinese Christian (Protestant)
Church reveal that China has 18,000 clerics, including over 2,000
ministers, also including over 300 female ministers.
</P>
<P>
The country has either refurbished or constructed over 600
churches every year since the 1980s. China has over 12,000
churches and 25,000 places of worship distributed throughout the
nation, especially in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Christian Church ranks first in the world in the
number of Bibles printed yearly, with a total of 20 million Bibles
published and distributed in China since 1980.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has consistently implemented
preferential policies covering the publication of Bibles,
including the granting of tax exemptions, according to Ye.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
