<HEADLINE> Water Official Blames Human Neglect For Some Flood Disasters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Vice Minister of Water Resources
Zhou Wenzhi blamed some localities' neglect for disasters caused
in the flood season.
</P>
<P>
The official said that some places built beer breweries, power
plants and other industrial projects in the river courses and
other places are cultivating the shores of lakes for agricultural
purposes, suffering severe damages in the current flood season.
</P>
<P>
He said that some companies also draw sand from the river
courses, which pose a danger to the safety of river banks.
</P>
<P>
He called on local governments concerned to take tough actions
in accordance with the Anti-flood Law to prevent such actions from
happening again.
</P>
<P>
He said that 21 provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities have suffered from floods, with Jiangxi, Fujian,
Hunan, Anhui, Guangxi, Zhejiang and Hubei the worst
affected. 
</P>
