<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain is intensifying its
promotional activities in China's mainland and further exploring
the giant market there in response to the growing demand for
quality Spanish products, Spain's Trade Commissioner in Hong Kong
Ernesto Tejedor said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 Spanish manufacturers and exhibitors had come to
Hong Kong to participate in the Asia Pacific Leather Fair and V&AMP;S,
the first international wine and spirit exhibition in the
Asia-Pacific.
</P>
<P>
Many Spanish exhibitors were pleased to receive new orders from
China and to strike deals with local suppliers to expand
distribution networks, Tejedor said.
</P>
<P>
Trade between Spain and China has been rising steadily. Hong
Kong is an important re-export center for trade between Spain and
China. Spanish re-exports to China through Hong Kong in 1997
reached 300 million U.S. dollars while Hong Kong exports of
products of China origin to Spain last year were valued at 1.3
billion U.S. dollars, according to statistics provided by the
Spanish Trade Commission here.
</P>
<P>
Looking to the future, the Spanish Commission and the Spanish
Institute for Foreign Trade will continue to enhance links between
Spain, Hong Kong and China's mainland. Efforts will be made to
promote joint ventures with Chinese companies and a number of
trade activities are being planned, including holding a fair named
"Expo Consumo" in the year 2000 in Shanghai, the Spanish
commissioner added. 
