<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: HK's Situation "So Far So Good": U.S. Envoy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Richard Boucher, consul-general
of the United States in Hong Kong, said Friday that Hong Kong has
had a "very successful year" in getting off the ground and the
situation here one year after it returned to China is "so far so
good."
</P>
<P>
In a group interview with Xinhua and local media in Hong Kong,
Boucher said that what everybody talked about a year ago was
whether the policies of "one country, two systems", a high degree
of autonomy and Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong could be
successfully implemented in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
But today "we don't discuss (that) much any more because the
answer is so clear," Boucher said.
</P>
<P>
Clearly the Central Government of China has honored its
commitment, Boucher said. "The central leadership had again and
again discouraged any interference in Hong Kong's affairs."
</P>
<P>
The representatives of the Central Government in Hong Kong have
carried out their foreign affairs and defense functions and not
got involved in other things, he said.
</P>
<P>
So, the "one country, two systems" has had a good start in Hong
Kong, Boucher said.
</P>
<P>
"But also the people of Hong Kong, the government of Hong Kong
have demonstrated they can indeed not just handle their affairs
well but cope and act with confidence on some very very difficult
issues," the consul-general noted.
</P>
<P>
"As we approach the first anniversary (of Hong Kong's return to
China), I think we all have to agree that Hong Kong has had quite
a year, but, really, a very successful year in getting off the
ground and coping with the turbulence in the region."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
