<HEADLINE> Green Campaign To Be Launched In New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to bring down the
pollution level in India's capital, the Municipal Corporation of
Delhi (MCD) has decided to launch a Green Delhi Campaign from July
2.
</P>
<P>
The Campaign, under which 650,000 trees and shrubs will be
planted across the city, was scheduled to coincide with the
expected first spell of monsoon, Delhi mayor Yog Dhyan Ahuja told
a press conference Friday.
</P>
<P>
Plantation would be done on road-sides, municipal institutions,
group housing societies, banks of drains, parks, traffic islands,
sanitary landfill sites and other open large spaces, he said.
</P>
<P>
The MCD had also launched a new scheme under which the parks,
green strips and central verges would be allotted to various
associations, corporate sectors, non-government organizations and
environmental groups for their upkeep and maintenance.
</P>
<P>
Ahuja said these organizations would also supply tree guards
for protection of saplings.
</P>
<P>
MCD Commissioner V. K. Duggal said at the press conference that
an action plan had been drawn to keep proper monitoring systems
and accountability of staff engaged in the green campaign task.
</P>
</TEXT>
