Health Minister Christos Solomis announced on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference to mark the United Nations World
Anti-Drug Day, Solomis said the Health Ministry has drafted a bill
on drug abuse and would submit it to the House of Representatives
for approval.
</P>
<P>
Drug abuse in Cyprus is on the increase, he said.
</P>
<P>
A study has shown that 4-5 percent of the Cypriots aged between
14-18 years have tried soft drugs like hashish or marijuana at
least once, according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Cypriot Police Chief Panicos Hadjiloizou announced
that the police launched a week-long anti-drug campaign on Friday
to fight against drug abuse, particularly among people aged
between 21-35.
</P>
<P>
Hadjiloizou said the Police Drug Squad has been enlarged by 60
percent since the beginning of the year to cope with the
increasing problem of drug abuse in Cyprus with an emphasis on
prevention and treatment of drug addicts. 
</P>
