<HEADLINE> Picture Album on Sino-U.S. Ties Published in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A large-size photo album depicting
President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States last year and
China's preparations for U.S. President Clinton's ongoing trip has
been published in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The picture album, with articles and captions in both Chinese
and English languages, will be given free to all guests
participating in the activities during President Bill Clinton's
visit to China and all journalists covering the event.
</P>
<P>
With the formation of a strategic partnership between China and
the United States, the album titled the "Chinese Talents" --
Specially Made for the Enhancement of Sino-U.S. Ties, gives a
multi-dimensional perspective of the consensus reached by both
sides through dialogues from a political, economic and cultural
angles, epitomizing the Chinese leader's wisdom and charisma.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it has also released for the first time a host of
details and inside episodes on the annals of bilateral ties since
little has been made known to the public.
</P>
<P>
The album has collected more than 350 photos with 52 articles.
It focuses on President Jiang's visit to the United States in
October last year apart from a coverage of all the major events
that have occurred in the history of Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Compilers of the album had exclusive interviews with a large
number of distinguished figures, both Chinese and foreign, such as
former U.S. President George Bush, former U.S. Secretaries of
State Warren Christopher, Cyrus Vance and Henry Kissinger, and the
incumbent Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, U.S. Ambassador
to China James Sasser, Anna Chan Chennault, presidents of leading
American businesses such as those related to Ford, Boeing, Intel,
Microsoft and Dupont, and former Chinese Ambassadors to the U.S.
Li Daoyu and Chai Zemin, former Chinese Ambassador to the U.N.
Ling Qing.
</P>
<P>
The album, published by the Hongqi (Red Flag) Publishing House,
will be distributed worldwide shortly. 
</P>
