<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Disaster
Prevention and Preparedness Commission said Friday food and
materials have been distributed to displaced people in northern
Tigray and Afar regions.
</P>
<P>
The commission was quoted by a report here as saying that
7,000 tons of food grains, 500 tons of nutritious food, 352 tons
of edible oil, 70,000 clothes, 20,000 blankets and 221 tents and
plastic sheetings have been distributed to displaced persons in
Tigray region.
