<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Faces Aggravated Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
will face even more severe flood conditions due to continuing
heavy forecast for the region.
</P>
<P>
Water levels along the Yangtze River and its tributaries
continue to rise on a daily basis and are already well above
warning levels. All reservoirs are filled to capacity and many are
releasing excess water into drainage areas.
</P>
<P>
The province has witnessed heavy flooding due to torrential
rains which have hit the region since June 12. Flooding has
affected over seven million residents and destroyed some 200,000
rooms, in addition to disrupting traffic on 170 highways.
</P>
<P>
A report issued by the Provincial Health Department reports
that flooded areas remain free of major outbreaks of endemic
diseases and food poisoning. However, numerous cases of diarrhoea,
colds and skin infections have been reported.
</P>
<P>
The report indicated that 800-odd medical teams staffed over
5,000 personnel have distributed more that 10,000 kilograms of
disinfectants, antibiotics and various other drugs, in addition
to over 100,000 leaflets explaining disease prevention
measures. Medical personnel have also offered demonstrations on
the proper use of medicine.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangxi Red Cross Society has distributed medical
products valued at 230,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
