<HEADLINE> President Clinton Arrives at Diaoyutai State Guesthouse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton and
his official delegation arrived at the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse,
where they will stay while in Beijing, at 9:14 (local time)
this evening.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to the United States Li Zhaoxing and his
wife accompanied President and Mrs. Clinton to the guesthouse from
the airport.
</P>
<P>
Staff members of the state guesthouse presented bouquets of
flowers to the president and Mrs. Clinton.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton and his delegation on Thursday arrived in
Xi'an on the first leg of his nine-day state visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Building No.18 of the guesthouse, which serves as residence of
visiting heads of state to China, was refurbished last March.
According to a source with the guesthouse, President Clinton has
come with a big official delegation. "We have made everything
ready for the arrival of this large party and will do our best to
render them first-rate service," the source said.
</P>
<P>
Diaoyutai, meaning "fishing terrace," was once an imperial
mansion with a history of more than 800 years. The Chinese
government in 1959 turned this place into a state guesthouse to
accommodate leaders of various countries who came to attend the
celebrations of the tenth anniversary of new China.
</P>
<P>
With the ancient Diaoyutai garden as the mainstay, the complex
which now has 19 villas of different architectural styles is a
high-grade venue for receiving high-ranking state guests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
