<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Rebounds Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices picked up a bit on
Singapore stock market Friday as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index (STII) gained 15.76 points to close at 1,085.59
points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the boost, led by property stocks, was encouraged
by unconfirmed rumors that the much-anticipated off-budget
measures to be announced Monday would revive the beleaguered
property market.
</P>
<P>
But they said Friday's late lift in sentiment was not
representative and the off-budget measures are still expected to
be met with a great deal of skepticism from the market.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 137.80 million shares, valued at
216.31 million Singapore dollars (about 129.53 million U.S.
dollars). Gainers led losers by 175 to 121 while 292 stocks
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The most active stock was ITE Elec which ended with a volume of
14.10 million shares traded. It was followed by the Easyknit thk
which had 10.80 million units traded. DBS Land was next with 9.00
million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
OCBC F was the top gainer of the day as it increased by 35
cents to close at 5.75 Singapore dollars. CityDev finished 34
cents up to 4.70 Singapore dollars. DBS increased by 30 cents to
end at 6.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it lost
70 cents to finish at 21.30 Singapore dollars. Genting ended at
3.12 Singapore dollars and YTL closed at 1.28 Singapore dollars.
Both of them lost 22 cents. 
</P>
