<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday due to the yen's
continued weakness which resulted in the local currency unit --
ringgit breaching the 4.00 level against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
At the close, when the ringgit closed the day at 4.0300/400
against the greenback, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index
which saw strong support around the 440 level closed 2.75 points
lower at 445.67.
</P>
<P>
The all share Emas Index dropped 0.86 of a point to 113.89, the
Industrial Index rose 1.45 points to 891.39 and the Second Board
Index fell 0.67 of a point to 98.65.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 322 to 204, while 183 counters
were unchanged, 214 untraded and 29 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 113.668 million shares valued at
265.607 million ringgit (about 65.9074 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 90.985 million shares valued at 165.167 million ringgit
(about 40.984 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
