worth 257.045 million ringgit (about 63.782 million dollars) from
86.922 million valued at 159.012 million ringgit (about 39.457
million dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover rose to 5.456 million shares valued
at 8.562 million ringgit (about 2.124 million dollars) from 4.063
million shares worth 6.155 million ringgit (about 1.527 million
dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals soared to 18.237 million stocks worth 22.038
million ringgit (about 5.468 million dollars) from Thursday's
2.989 million valued at 10.455 million ringgit (about 2.594
million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.411
million shares traded, industrial products 12.851 million shares,
construction 11.393 million shares, trading/services 46.796
million shares, infrastructure 615,000 shares, finance 20.442
million shares, hotels 263,000 shares, properties 11.227 million
shares, plantation 5.397 million shares, mining 214,000 shares,
trusts 100,000 shares, closed/fund 24,000 shares and loans 10.478
million shares. 
