<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Further Cuts Oil Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government announced
Thursday a further cut of 100,000 barrels per day in its crude
oil production as part of international efforts to stabilize oil
prices.
</P>
<P>
With the announcement, Nigeria's daily oil output now stands
at 2.033 million barrels per day.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria in March this year cut its production by 125,000
barrels per day, in the face of a falling oil price.
</P>
<P>
The new reduction in production, part of the 2.6 million
barrels per day agreed upon by the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC), was announced at the on-going OPEC
meeting in Vienna, Austria, Nigeria's Petroleum Resources
Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new reduction will take effect from next month and will be
valid for one year.
</P>
<P>
OPEC Member countries have pledged their commitment to the
agreement, a ministry statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
