<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Urges United Position Against Israel's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Leader Yasser Arafat
sent urgent letters from Ramallah, West Bank on Friday to Arab and
Islamic organizations, urging them to take urgent measures to
protect the holy city of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Arafat sent his urgent letters to King Hassan II of Morocco,
Arab League Council and the presidency of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference, asking them to adopt a united Arab and
Islamic position to encounter Israel's expansion scheme in
Jerusalem, according to Jerusalem Media and Communication Center
(JMCC).
</P>
<P>
He decided to send the urgent letters after chairing a
Palestinian leadership meeting Thursday night in Ramallah which
discussed the latest political developments in light of the
dangerous crisis in the peace process, because of the Israeli
policies of expansion in Arab East Jerusalem and other settlements
in the occupied territories at the expense of the Palestinian
lands, JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
Israel announced last Thursday its Jerusalem expansion plan,
under which the Ma'ale Adumim and other Jewish settlements in the
West Bank will be included into Jerusalem municipality.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians strongly criticized the plan, saying that
it is a declaration of war against the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Arafat met Friday in Ramallah with an Israel Arab
delegation, during which he said that Israeli expansion measures
in Jerusalem area blatant violation of international resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Head of the delegation Adbul Wahab Darawshe, who is also member
of the Israel's Knesset (parliament) from the United Arab List
which has four Knesset members, told Arafat that his party is
against the Jerusalem expansion plan and will try its best to
prevent it from implementing.
</P>
<P>
JMCC's another report said that from Friday morning, Israeli
authorities closed the northern entrance to Ramallah district of
the West Bank, banning Palestinians from entering or leaving
through that entrance without giving reasons.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities also erected checkpoints near Beit El
settlement on the way between Ramallah and Nablus, another West
Bank city, on the way to Birzeit town and near Attara Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leadership comprises executive members of
the Palestine Liberation Organization and the cabinet members of
the Palestinian National Authority.
</P>
<P>
Arafat accepted resignations of the cabinet ministers on
Wednesday pending for a cabinet reshuffle. But all ministers have
become care-takers of their respective ministries till the new
cabinet is formed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
