<HEADLINE> Injured Nigerian Star Could Miss Rest of Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Injured Nigerian player Daniel
Amokachi may miss the rest of the World Cup finals, the Nigerian
coach Bora Milutinovic said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian team doctors said they thought Amokachi's chances of
recovering in time for further games were slim.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Amokachi sustained a knee injury in training
four days before Nigeria's opening game against Spain. He played 66
minutes in the 1-0 win over Bulgaria and was due to have captained
the team against Paraguay on Wednesday until he aggravated the injury
in the warm-up.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria will play Denmark in a second round match on Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
