<HEADLINE> Italian Captain Maldini Turns 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Italian captain Paolo Maldini, a
backbone of the team's defence, turned 30 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Maldini, who will win his 91st international apperance when Italy
faces Norway on Saturday, has spent two of his birthdays during the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
He had been 22 in Rome the day after Italy beat Uruguay in the
second round of the 1990 edition.
</P>
<P>
During 1994 World Cup finals, his 26th birthday came three days
after Italy beat Norway in the first round.
</P>
<P>
Maldini, son of Italian coach Cesare Maldini, had said he wanted to
postpone this birthday's celebration after repeating their 1994 win
over Norway. 
</P>
