<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Approves Two Laws (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China's highest legislative body
today approved the Law on Doctors, the Laws on Exclusive
Economic Zones and Continental Shelves and various other important
proposals.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), presided over this afternoon's
meeting and delivered a speech to members of the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Approval of the Law on Exclusive Economic Zones and Continental
Shelves is highly significant for enabling the country to
effectively safeguard its sovereignty and jurisdiction over seas
and marine resources, said Li.
</P>
<P>
The Law on Doctors urges Chinese medical personnel to
improve their skills and professional ethics, as well as protect
their legitimate rights, according to Li.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the NPC Standing Committee deliberated the draft
revision of the Land-Use Law which was preliminarily deliberated
during the second meeting of the Standing Committee in April.
</P>
<P>
The existing Land-Use Law is regarded unsuitable for the
current market economy and ongoing reform.
</P>
<P>
The coverage of farmland has continued to shrink in recent
years, with various localities wasting valuable land and natural
resources.
</P>
<P>
In order to effectively curb the misuse of farmland, the
revised Land-Use Law will effectively curb the misuse of farmland
by strictly controlling the different uses for agricultural,
construction and idle land.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
