<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Approves Two Laws (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The draft law requires the state to adopt special policies to
protect farmland resources and strictly prevents cultivatable land
from being transferred to other uses.
</P>
<P>
Li called for tougher punishment for any violation of the
Land-Use law.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee also deliberated the final accounts
report for fiscal year 1997 presented by Finance Minister Xiang
Huaicheng and the audit report for the 1997 state budget submitted
by Auditor-General Li Jinhua.
</P>
<P>
Supervising the state budget is an extremely important job for
the NPC and its Standing Committee, said Li.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Standing Committee approved the reports and
tabled suggestions on macro-control of the economy and reform of
the taxation system.
</P>
<P>
The country must work diligently to surmount difficulties
resulting from the financial crisis affecting some Asian
countries, said Li.
</P>
<P>
He added that the NPC Standing Committee plans to publish and
solicit general public opinions of the Draft Law on the
Organization of Village Committees.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee also approved the Extradition
Treaty between the People's Republic of China and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day meeting, Li joined NPC vice-chairpersons in
group discussions concerning deliberation of the draft laws and
the other proposals.
</P>
<P>
He also called for improved coordination between various NPC
committees. 
