<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: "One Country, Two Systems" Takes Roots in HK (1) By Feng Xiuju </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- "One country, two systems" is
generally believed to have taken roots in the heart of people here
since Hong Kong became a Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China on July 1 last year.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with this principle, Hong Kong enjoys a high
degree of autonomy and retains its own separate legal system,
complete with its court of final appeal. Hong Kong's previous
capitalist social and economic systems and way of life remain
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law, Hong Kong residents enjoy freedom
of speech, of the press and of publication; freedom of
association, of assembly, of procession and of demonstration.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed that from last July 1 to March 31,
there had been over 1,260 public demonstrations in Hong Kong and
626 societies formed.
</P>
<P>
Backed by the 6.5 million Hong Kong people, the government of
the Hong Kong SAR headed by Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa has
done its utmost to ward off the economic difficulties brought on
by the year-long Asian financial turmoil and maintained Hong
Kong's stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Under the "one country, two systems" principle, Hong Kong
retains its status as an international financial, trade, shipping
and information center and one of the safest cities in the world.
</P>
<P>
As the world's busiest container port for six consecutive
years, Hong Kong handled about 14.6 million twenty-foot equivalent
units (TEUs) of containers in 1997.
</P>
<P>
At the end of May this year, Hong Kong's foreign exchange
reserve totaled 96.4 billion U.S. dollars, ranking third in the
world and first on a per capita basis.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been regarded as the second among the cities with
competitiveness in the world, according to a report issued by the
World Economic Forum in this month.
</P>
<P>
Compared with 1996, the overall crime rate and violent crime
rate in 1997 dropped by 17.3 percent and 12.4 percent
respectively, the lowest in 24 years.
</P>
<P>
All this shows that the "one country, two systems" concept
first put forward by the late Deng Xiaoping is working well in
Hong Kong. Even those who doubted whether the principle would be
implemented before Hong Kong's return to China have come to
realize that this principle is "scientific, practicable and
successful".
</P>
<P>
To a certain degree, the key to turning the "one country, two
systems" concept into reality depends on the full implementation
of the principles of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" with a
high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
As Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa put it, "The Central People's
Government has granted us a high degree of autonomy -- a situation
that is unparalleled anywhere in the world."
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, since the Hong Kong SAR was established a
year ago, not a single official has been sent by the Central
People's Government to the SAR government which was formed in
accordance with the relevant stipulations of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The Central Government has fully respected the SAR government
in the belief that the Hong Kong people are bound to administer
Hong Kong well.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
