<HEADLINE> Macao to Cut Government Expenditure: Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
said on Thursday night that the Macao Government will cut its
administrative expenditure and suspend some public engineering
projects in the face of economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The Government Information Office quoted the governor as saying
after returning from a working visit to Portugal that because of
the economic difficulties in the wake of the Asian financial
turmoil, the government will trim its budget and suspend some
public engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that a budget reduction proportion will be
announced soon for all government departments, but there will be
different reduction proportions for different departments.
</P>
<P>
However, the governor said there will be no cut in the salary
of civil servants.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been affected by an economic slow-down since
1993. But the Asian financial storms have made it worse. Tourist
arrivals and exports, two of its leading income makers, have
dropped substantially over the past several months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
