<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of Macao-Zhuhai Bridge to Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Macao and neighboring Zhuhai
authorities in south China's Guangdong Province will launch the
construction of a link bridge separately next Monday, the Macao
Government Information Office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
To be named "Lotus Flower Bridge" after the symbol on the flag
of the future Macao Special Administrative Region, the bridge will
connect Macao's Taipa Island and Zhuhai's Hengqin Island.
</P>
<P>
The 1.3-kilometer-long bridge will open a second land crossing
apart from the existing border gate to China's inland, after it is
completed in about 15 months before the handover ceremony on
December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
There will be a ribbon-cutting ceremony on each side of the
bridge next Monday. The two sides share the costs of the bridge of
200 million patacas (about 25 million U.S. dollars). The bridge
will have six traffic lanes.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the bridge was decided by the
Sino-Portuguese Infrastructure Coordination Commission (SPICC)
earlier this month. Chinese Officials described the bridge as
important for both Macao and Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
"It will help improve Macao's outward land transportation
conditions and facilitate the development of Macao's islands and
Zhuhai's Hengqin Island," Xie Houhe, chief of SPICC Chinese
delegation, said earlier.
</P>
<P>
The SPICC is now considering construction of some other
infrastructure projects by the two sides. Further discussions will
be made on the projects including the extension to Macao a
Guangzhou-Zhuhai railway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
