<HEADLINE> Drugs Burned In Northeastern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- About 85 kilograms of drugs were
burned in the open today in Shenyang, the capital of China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
These drugs were seized during the anti-drug campaigns of the
past few years, and included heroin, opium, and "ice", according
to Li Feng, the vice-director of the Provincial Public Security
Department.
</P>
<P>
Local police have solved 5,315 cases of drug dealing or use
since last April, and have arrested 8,168 people and forced more
than 3,100 addicts to give up the habit. 
</P>
