<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovak Bank Opens First China Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Vseobecna Uverova Banka of
Slovakia opened a representative office in this financial and
trade center of China Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that a Slovak bank opened an office in
China.
</P>
<P>
Founded on the basis of a state bank of the former
Czechoslovakia in January 1990, Vseobecna Uverova Banka was
restructured into a joint-stock bank in 1992 with state-owned
foundations holding a 51 percent stake and collective and private
investors the remaining 49 percent. The bank had 4.9 billion US
dollars in total assets by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Jan Gabriel, the chairman and president, said that Vseobecna
Uverova Banka is optimistic about China's economic prospects.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the Shanghai office is intended not only to
provide services to the Chinese banking community, enterprises and
the public, but also to help boost economic and trade cooperation
between Slovakia and China, said Gabriel, who was here to attend a
ceremony marking the opening of the representative office.
</P>
<P>
Besides the new office, the Slovak bank has two more overseas
offices, in Moscow and London. 
</P>
</TEXT>
