<HEADLINE> 200 English Fans Banned from Going to Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 English football fans
were banned from going to Paris from Thursday night to Friday
morning, said the French frontier police DICCILEC.
</P>
<P>
Among the fans, many of whom were already drunk, three were
detained for carrying 168 bottles of beer and four liters of vodka.
</P>
<P>
The fans were intercepted by police in Calais and in the Gare
du Nord railway station in Paris, the destination of the Euro-star
train from London.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 62 English fans were banned from entering France
from Belgium Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Some of them were trying to get to Lens, where the English
football team will play Colombia Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Violent clashes took place between the fans, some of them
drunk, and Belgian police in the city of Ostende near the French
border Thursday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
