<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drugs Destroyed In Chongqing, Suzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- To mark the International
Anti-drug Day and to show its determination to fight drugs, the
city of Chongqing, in southwestern China, burned 63 kg of heroin,
one kg of opium, and 33 kg of poppy buds today.
</P>
<P>
Near the Golden Triangle, Chongqing has been chosen by drug
traffickers as an ideal transit place, with an increasing number
of drug abusers.
</P>
<P>
Police have been cracking down on drug-related crimes and,
between last June and this May, solved 3,000 drug trafficking
cases and confiscated more than 70 kg of heroin.
</P>
<P>
In Suzhou, a scenic city in eastern China's Jiangsu Province,
more than 60 kg of drugs were burned today, with 1,000 college
students and other locals watching. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
