<HEADLINE> Indonesia, ADB Sign Loan Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government will get
another soft loan from the Asian Development Bank (ADB) worth
nearly 1.5 billion U.S. dollars, which is payable in 15 years with
a three-year grace period.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the loan was signed by Finance Minister Bambang
Subianto and ADB Vice President Peter Sullivan here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Subianto told reporters that 1.4 billion dollars of the amount
will be used to finance the import of eligible items and to
sustain the country's foreign exchange reserves and the state
budget.
</P>
<P>
Another 50 million dollars will be used for technical
assistance to strengthen the country's financial system and
improve human resources, while the remaining 47 million dollars
will be used for development loan for housing (secondary mortgage
facility), Subianto added. 
</P>
