<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.-based Internet Society
(ISOC) will host training workshops for more than 250 developing
countries' professionals from July 11 to 19 in Geneva and in Rio
de Janeiro of Brazil, ISOC said Friday.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first time the workshops will be held in two
locations simultaneously, ISOC also said.
</P>
<P>
