<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host 50th PATA Conference in 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will host the 50th
annual conference of the Pacific Asia Travel Association or Pata,
the world's grandest tourism event, in the year 2001, Culture,
Arts and Tourism Minister Sabbaruddin Chik said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting scheduled for April 22-26 of that year would see
the gathering of 2,000 Pata members comprising chiefs of state-
and city-owned tourism promotion agencies and cruise shipping
companies, among others, Sabbaruddin told a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
"The participants would discuss current problems facing world
tourism and draw up strategies to meet the members' demand to
secure a competitive edge in marketing tourist products and
destinations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sabbaruddin said the theme "Blazing the Tourism Trail in The
New Millennium" has been chosen for the 50th Pata conference.
</P>
<P>
Preceding it, Malaysia would also host the 13th Pata Chapters
World Congress over three days starting April 18, 2001, he said.
</P>
<P>
Pata, set up in 1951, now has 2,100 member organizations in the
hospitality industry world-wide, including 101 government-run
tourism agencies as well as those of states and cities. Its other
members are 17,000 individuals and chapters.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia had hosted the 1972 and 1986 Pata conferences and the
two events prompted the establishment of the Tourism Development
Corporation and the Culture, Arts and Tourism Ministry
respectively to develop Malaysia's tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Sabbaruddin said he is confident that the 2001 Pata conference
would again highlight Malaysia's position as the region's top
tourist convention venue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
