<HEADLINE> Export Market for Zambia's Agro Produce Expands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The demand for Zambia's rice,
cotton and soya beans is on increase in Tunisia, Denmark, Iran
and China, said a latest export review of the Zambia Export
Board.
</P>
<P>
The three crops will earn Zambia unspecified million U.S.
Dollars annually, thus spurring growth in the shrinking sector,
Times of Zambia Friday quoted the export board's reveiw as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
Zambia will export over 50,000 tonnes of soya
bean meal to Tunisia. And in Denmark, firms are placing orders
totalling 75 tonnes of crude soya bean oil and 20 tonnes of crude
soya bean oil, said the publication.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese firm will import a total of 25,000 tonnes of Zambian
rice.
</P>
<P>
Iranian firms have also shown interest in importing cotton
yarn and polyester textured yarn denier from zambia.
</P>
<P>
The expanding export market for Zambia's agricultural produce
will increase the country's much-needed foreign exchange
earnings and spur an agricultural growth.  
</P>
