<HEADLINE> One Helicopter Crashed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lanka's helicopter crashed
about one km south east of Vavuniya air field in the Northern
Province of the country Friday morning, killing four persons
aboard, according to military spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink dewage said this helicopter was being positioned
along with another helicopter at Vavuniya to provide air support
for operation of government troops. The MI 24 helicopter had four
crew members aboard and all were killed during the crash.
</P>
<P>
He said the helicopter was totally destroyed by fire after the
crash.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is not yet established, said Dewage,
adding that a court of inquiry has been appointed to inquire into
the incident. 
