<HEADLINE> Investing In Forests In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Investors have shown growing
interests in forests and related businesses in south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that farmers, organizations, private business
people, and overseas investors have been reclaiming mountain areas
for forests and have started forest-related businesses.
</P>
<P>
In 16 major cities involved in the forest industry, 270
orchards have been built since late last year on 60,000 hectares
of reclaimed land. In Shaoguan, there are 265 joint-ownership
forest farms on 183,333 hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Businesses include pulpwood, fruit and lumber. Overseas
investment has been used in 52 forestry projects, involving 850
million U.S. dollars worth of contracts, and 118 million
U.S. dollars paid in.
</P>
<P>
There are 8 foreign-backed forest and fruit-bearing projects
with 283 million U.S. dollars worth of contracts on 241,300
hectares of forest and 2,267 hectares of fruit trees. 
</P>
