<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Catches Up In Fixed-Asset Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan Province
has revised its planned fixed-investment figure.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to increase its planned fixed investment by
10-to-12 billion yuan to 118-to-120 billion yuan. The final
figures are an increase of 23-to-26 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
To secure the funds, Sichuan plans to issue debts, raise prices
for water supply in cities in addition to issuing more loans.
</P>
<P>
The province will also allow foreigners to participate in a
wider area of economic construction, and expand experimentation
with BOT (build, operate, transfer) projects by foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan's per-capita investment for infrastructure construction
is 675 yuan, 55.8 percent lower than the national average.
</P>
