<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian coach Mario Zagallo
supported captain Dunga after the midfielder and Bebeto had a
dispute in the match against Morocco.
</P>
<P>
"The dspute between Dunga and Bebeto has in no way affected
Dunga's leadership role. He remains the leader of the team without a
doubt." said Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo said he knew Chile and respect them:"Chile play 3-5-2.
They have two good wingers and we must remain careful while at the
same time keeping our rhythm."
</P>
<P>
Brazil will play against Chile in the round of 16 at Parc des
Princes stadium on Saturday. 
</P>
