<HEADLINE> Croatia's Prosinecki Wants to Make to Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Croatia midfielder Prosinecki has said
his team was now setting their eyes on the biggest trophy -- the World
Cup.
</P>
<P>
"I'd like our team to make it to the quarter-finals. Or, let's be
honest, the final itself," he said Wednesday in Vittel, France.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We could do really well, because we've got the players...
We're mature and whichever teams we meet in the next few games, we're
ready to face any of them."
</P>
<P>
Prosinecki, who plays for Croatian club Zagreb, said nothing was in
the bag despite the fact that they had qualified for the second round.
</P>
<P>
"We have to conslidate and reward all our efforts by winning. It's
vital to stay concentrated and vigilant and give our very best as to
win and finish top of our group."
</P>
<P>
Croatia, who already enter the last 16 along with Argentina, will
meet the former world champions later on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The winners of the game will finish atop group H while a draw will
mean Argentina win the group.
</P>
<P>
"There is no doubt that the match against Argentina is important,"
Prosinecki said. "They are a very strong team and we know what we're
up against. The players belong to the best teams in the world."
</P>
<P>
He added, "For me, this World Cup is the best I've ever seen with a
very high standard. There are no 'lesser' teams. They are all
dangerous." 
</P>
