<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Accelerates Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
will bring the total highway mileage in the province to 60,000
kilometers (km) by 2000, a provincial government official
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The length of expressway roads will reach 927 km and that of
highway roads in rural townships and counties will surpass 46,000
km.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou, the provincial capital, will become a transportation
hub with two railway trunk lines and two expressway roads meeting.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province ranks fourth in China in highway
mileage with the total length reaching 55,000 km. Nearly 99
percent of villages are connected with the provincial or national
highway network.
</P>
<P>
In the upcoming three years, it will renovate 2,430 km of roads
and build 8,000 km of new roads in rural areas at an estimated
cost of 25 billion yuan. It plans to provide 97 percent of its
rural areas with access to highways by 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
