<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Put Mao, Deng, Jiang in One Movie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China is planning to have Mao
Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and Jiang Zemin -- representing three
generations of the leadership of the Communist Party of China --
appear in one feature movie for the first time.
</P>
<P>
An official at China's Film Bureau told Xinhua today that the
film, "Dream of the Century," is about the Three Gorges Dam
project which was the result of "brilliant and foresighted
decisions by these leaders".
</P>
<P>
She said the directors will decide whether they should employ
actors to play the three leaders or use documentary clips.
</P>
<P>
Chinese actors have played Mao Zedong and Deng Xiaoping in a
series of movies. Some of the movies had been shown while Deng was
alive.
</P>
<P>
The new film will be a product of a husband-wife team,
directors Li Qiankuan and Xiao Guiyun, who have made several
expensive films about Mao and Deng in wartime.
</P>
<P>
"Dream of the Century" will be based on historical events,
sources said. The story would begin in 1946 when the Chinese
government employed a U.S. expert to study the feasibility of the
dam, and ends in 1997 when the course of the Yangtze River was
blocked to erect the dam.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges project will be the largest hydro-power
station in the world. There have been widespread disputes about
the project, which will be discussed in the movie, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The film is expected to be shot by the Hubei Film Studio and
will be used to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
