<HEADLINE> At Least 30 Arrested as Fans Clash with Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 30 people have been arrested
late on Thursday when drunken English fans clashed with French police
in Lens and Lille.
</P>
<P>
Police said 15 English fans were detained in Lens after a group of
about 100 drunken and chanting fans threw beer cans and glasses at
riot police outside several bars.
</P>
<P>
In Lille, northern France's biggest railway junction, police were
facing the similiar situation when they had to arrest similiar number
of fans, most of them English, after a bar owner harassed by them
called the police.
</P>
<P>
Lille local authorities have asked the bars to close for 24 hours
from 9 o'clock in the morning on Friday to prevent the fans to obtain
alcohol in the day when England meet Colombia in their last group
game.
</P>
<P>
Lille also slammed a ban on the sale of takeaway alcohol, a measure
against a possible stock-up by the fans.
</P>
<P>
Alcohol is not allowed to be consumed in the open while all bars,
restaurants and shops will refuse to sell to the supporter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
