<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The World Bank (WB) agreed here Thursday to
provide 348.8 million U.S. dollars for four development projects
in four African countries.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 150 million dollars goes to Algeria's
low-income housing project to help improve living conditions in
selected urban slums and other areas. (WB-Africa)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukraine's Vice Foreign Minister Vladimir Handogy said
Thursday that the first round of negotiations on measures of
building military trust in the Black Sea region was
"unprecedented."
</P>
<P>
A communique following the talks on Tuesday and Wednesday said
that the adoption and implementation of these measures would
support economic cooperation between the littoral countries of the
Black Sea and strengthen security, peace and stability in the
region. The measures will not be directed against any third
country, it added. (Black-Sea-Negotiation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Richard Holbrooke, the U.S. envoy to the Balkan,
said here Thursday the international community opposes the
independence of Kosovo and admits the fact that Kosovo is part of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Holbrooke made the remarks while meeting with a group of
Yugoslav journalists at the U.S. embassy in Belgrade. Beforehand,
he held talks with Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic on
Kosovo. (Kosovo-Yugoslavia-Integrity)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Aleksander Avdeen
said Wednesday that negotiations based on the respect of
Yugoslavia's sovereign integrity and the Yugoslav Constitution are
the only solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Avdeen, who made the remark in Shkup, the capital city of
Macedonia, after meeting Macedonian leaders, said that he hoped
ethnic Albanians in Kosovo could control their sentiments and come
to the negotiating table. There is no other way out, he added.
(Russia-Kosovo) 
</P>
