<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Ends in Losses This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus stock market exhibited an
overall downward course in the past trading week, with four out of
five trading sessions ended in losses.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed at 421.7 points Thursday, a
weekly drop of 10.7 points compared with the previous trading
week, said the weekly review issued by the Cyprus Investment and
Securities Corporation Limited (CISCO) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The index in Monday's session finished 2.4 points higher from
last Friday to close at 429 points, but then tumbled through the
following three trading days.
</P>
<P>
This week also saw a lower turnover of 4.3 million Cyprus pounds
(about 8.6 million U.S. dollars) compared with last week's 5.2
million Cyprus pounds (about 10.4 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the review said that the current stocks price has
still held on a capital appreciation of 8.3 percent so far this
year. 
</P>
