<HEADLINE> United Technologies Intensifying Investment in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- United Technologies (UT), a
U.S. manufacturing giant, is intensifying its commitment in China
by setting up its 24th joint venture, this time with Shanghai
Electric Machinery Company (SEMC).
</P>
<P>
UT has its automobile subsidiary, UT Automotive Inc. (UTA),
holding 50 percent of the equity share in the Shanghai Ri Yong-UTA
Gate Electric Co. Ltd. with an initial investment 8.5 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, which was established Thursday, is expected
to become a market leader in the production of automotive cooling
fan modules in China with state-of-the-art motor and air-flow
technology from UTA's Gate subsidiary.
</P>
<P>
"The coupling of SEMC's manufacturing capability and market
share in China with UTA's advanced technology and reputation will
make this joint venture a market leader in the Chinese market, as
well as other areas of Asia," said Alan Winslow, president of
UTA's Asia-Pacific Operations.
</P>
<P>
Ma Baofa, general manager of the new company, said the
cooperation should help enhance the competitive edge of SEMC's old
brand "Shunda" in both domestic and overseas markets and lift its
export share in sales by 20 percent in five years.
</P>
<P>
The former Shanghai Ri Yong Electric Machinery Works is a
state-owned automotive cooling fan supplier under SEMC with 70
percent of domestic market share. It is also an exclusive supplier
of cooling fan modules and harnesses for Shanghai Volkswagen,
Audi, Citroen and Shanghai GM.
</P>
<P>
UT Automotive is a 3-billion-U.S.-dollar, supplier of
electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components
for car and light truck manufacturers. It has set up other joint
ventures -- two in Hubei Province and one in Tianjin -- totaling
an investment of more than 40 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its parent company is a multinational with products ranging from
aerospace, air-conditioning equipment and electric elevators to
automotive parts and components, among others.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
