<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Discusses Draft Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) this morning heard reports
on two proposed laws and a report on the final accounts of the
1997 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
At the ongoing third session of the NPC Standing Committee,
Wang Weicheng, chairman of the NPC Law Committee, delivered
reports on the revision of two draft laws on doctors and the
exclusive economic zones and continental shelves.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the current session should pass the revised
versions of the two draft laws which include the opinions of
members of the NPC Standing Committee and of the localities as
well as concerned departments and experts.
</P>
<P>
Guo Zhenqian, vice-chairman of the NPC Financial and Economic
Committee, delivered a report on the final accounts of the 1997
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
He said that the state revenue increased rapidly in 1997, with
control gained over total expenditures and expenditure patterns.
</P>
<P>
Guo said that the revenue out of the state financial budget was
mainly used to increase the grain risk fund, to invest in central
and western regions of the country, and to reduce the financial
deficit.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the current session of the NPC Standing
Committee should pass the final account of the 1997 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the first five months this year, the
implementation of the financial budget was not good, the result of
sluggish economic growth, poor operation of state-owned
enterprises and problems in tax collections.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of the year, he said, more efforts will be
made to strengthen revenue adjustment and control, increase
investment in economic and social development programs, and
strengthen tax collection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
