<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Banks to Increase Support for Small, Medium-sized Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
will adopt a series of policy measures to support the healthy
development of small and medium-sized enterprises, according to
Shang Fulin, vice-governor of the PBOC.
</P>
<P>
Shang said that the PBOC will issue a circular on financial
support to national economic development, which lists small and
medium-sized enterprises as well as township enterprises as the
key sectors to receive aid.
</P>
<P>
In the circular, the PBOC urges the Minsheng Bank of China,
city commercial banks and credit cooperatives to play a leading
role in supporting the small and medium-sized enterprises and
township enterprises. State-owned commercial banks, other
commercial banks and non-bank institutions should also actively
provide credit services for them in accordance with related
regulations, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The central bank demanded that loans should be extended to
small and medium-sized enterprises which have selling products,
make good profits, develop and use new technologies.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC urged all commercial banks to utilize various
financial tools with flexibility to provide settlement,
remittance, transfer of accounts, financial management and other
services for enterprises, and improve the financial service system
for small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC also is seeking solutions for small and medium-sized
enterprises' difficulties in using mortgage and guarantee loans,
Shang said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by state-owned commercial banks show that
at the end of March the outstanding amount of loans from
state-owned commercial banks to small and medium-sized enterprises
was 1.7 trillion yuan, about 38 percent of the total outstanding
amount of loans of state-owned commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has ratified the establishment of 79 city
commercial banks, and 73 others are being studied and should be
ratified soon. The Minsheng Bank, which mainly serves small and
medium-sized enterprises, started operations in 1996 and has so
far set up five branches and 14 sub-branches.
</P>
<P>
According to related statistics, more than 99 percent of
China's businesses are small and medium-sized enterprises which
contribute 60 percent of the country's total industrial output
value, 40 percent of its tax revenues and 75 percent of its total
work force.
</P>
<P>
During the last 20 years, the growth of small and medium-sized
enterprises have quadrupled that of large enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
