<HEADLINE> Hainan Accelerates Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Construction of 20 key
infrastructure projects planned for this year is proceeding
smoothly in south China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official reported that the projects will be
completed at a total cost 4.68 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Work on the Century Bridge in Haikou, the provincial capital,
commenced recently and is scheduled for completion on May 1,
2001. The six-lane bridge will be 2,663 meters long and 29.8
meters wide.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the island's ring road will be completed
one year ahead of schedule in July, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The 268-km eastern section of the ring road has opened to
traffic, and construction of the 366-km western section is
proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Hainan ranks first in the nations with an average 500 km of
roads per square kilometer. 
</P>
