<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Youths Urged to Join Drug Elimination Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar Minister of Home Affairs
Colonel Tin Hlaing Friday called on youths in the country to join
up in the battle against narcotic drugs and to totally eliminate
them in accordance with the theme -- Youths Uniting to Prevent
Drug Abuse -- adopted by the United Nations this year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a prize presentation ceremony of stories, poems,
articles, cartoons and songs contests honoring the International
Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking, Tin Hlaing, who
is also chairman of the Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control,
said the proliferation of the narcotic habit among youths spell a
disaster to all countries including Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
In the demand eradication aspect, he said, preventive education
and information are continuously disseminated to the students and
youths and the public in addition to treatment and rehabilitation
to drug addicts.
</P>
<P>
In the law enforcement aspect, he noted, not only narcotics
like opium, heroin, marijuana and stimulants are being seized in
the country but also clandestine laboratories producing them are
being increasingly ferreted out and destroyed.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the emergence of the Mongla opium-free zone in
the country's eastern Shan state last year to the cooperative
efforts of the local ethnic minorities, adding that plans are
underway to bring about more similar zones.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has laid down a two-point national strategy for
narcotic drug control -- to designate narcotic drug eradication
and prevention as a national duty and to gradually eliminate poppy
cultivation by raising the standard of living of the national
races in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
Three tactics of supply elimination, demand elimination and law
enforcement are employed to implement the strategies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
