<HEADLINE> Russia Stresses Principled Negotiations over Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister
Aleksander Avdeen said Wednesday that negotiations based on the
respect of Yugoslavia's sovereign integrity and the Yugoslav
Constitution are the only solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Avdeen made the remark in Shkup, the capital city of Macedonia,
after meeting Macedonian leaders, the Macedonian Press reported.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped ethnic Albanians in Kosovo could control their
sentiments and come to the negotiating table. There is no other
way out. The use of force cannot solve the Kosovo crisis, the
official stressed.
</P>
<P>
The key to the settlement of the issue is to grant autonomy to
Kosovo in line with international standards, Avdeen said. However,
the autonomy must be implemented within the Serbian Republic, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Avdeen criticized NATO threats to send forces to the border
area between Macedonia, Albania and Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
He opposed the threat of force, which is the basic principle of
the Yeltsin-Milosevic statement made public in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Avdeen, initiating a new round of diplomatic activities on
Kosovo, arrived in Shkup on Tuesday on a two-day visit following
his Albania tour.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people have been killed since the outbreak of
armed conflict between ethnic Albanians and Serb police in
Kosovo. The troubled province is now under the threat of escalated
and expanded conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
