<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Vows to Totally Eliminate Drugs in 15 years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will totally eliminate
poppy cultivation in 15 years, said Myanmar Minister of Home
Affairs Colonel Tin Hlaing Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony marking the International Day Against
Illicit Trafficking, Tin Hlaing, who is also chairman of the
Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control, said the period can be
shortened with assistance from external sources.
</P>
<P>
A baseline data collection project on poppy cultivation and
drug addicts is being implemented in the whole country starting
January this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been doing its best to eradicate narcotic drugs
with some achievements in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of this year, the Myanmar authorities
destroyed a dozen heroin refineries in Shan state in the northern
part of the country, following the destruction of 33 refineries in
the state in 1997, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,600 kilograms of narcotic drugs including more than 170
kg of heroin were also seized in the country by the enforcement
agencies with over 8,000 hectares of poppy plantations destroyed
in the same period.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the authorities confiscated a total of 15,146 kg of
narcotics including 1,401 kg of heroin and 7,883 kg of opium as
well as more than 5 million tablets of amphetamine stimulant, and
took action against 5,361 people involved in 3,864 drug-related
cases.
</P>
<P>
In the same year, Myanmar was able to turn the Mongla region in
eastern Shan state into an opium-free zone and efforts are being
made to bring about more similar zones.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has laid down a two-point national strategy for
narcotic drug control -- to designate narcotic drug eradication
and prevention as a national duty and to gradually eliminate poppy
cultivation by raising the standard of living of the ethnic groups
in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
Three tactics of supply elimination, demand elimination and law
enforcement are employed to implement the strategies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0274 </DOCNO>
