<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Legislature Ratifies Territorial Deal with Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian National Assembly approved
a territorial treaty Thursday intended to end long-time disputes
with Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The treaty, ratified by an overwhelming majority, spells out an
agreed line of demarkation between the two countries at the mouth
of the River Rezovska and the Black Sea.
</P>
<P>
The treaty is in the interest of Bulgaria and poses no
violation to the neighbors bordering the Black Sea, Bulgarian
newspaper, the Viewpoint quoted, a foreign ministry official as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The River Rezovska, originates in Turkey and extends for 112
kilometers, constitutes a part of the two countries' border
line. Bulgaria and Turkey have for decades disputed division of
the Black Sea river mouth. 
</P>
