<HEADLINE> Rectification Drive Achieves Initial Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The education and rectification
campaign has achieved initial success in procuratorial organs
nationwide, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
By June 10, provincial procuratorates had investigated 289
cases of violations of law and discipline, said Han Zhubin,
procurator-general of China's Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
Han was speaking yesterday in a country-wide televised
conference attended by local high-ranking procuratorial officials.
</P>
<P>
Of these cases, 183 had been wound up. Some 191 people had been
dealt with; 19 had been investigated in respect of criminal
responsibility, and the remainder had received Party and
administrative punishments.
</P>
<P>
Han praised the high efficiency reflected in the campaign at
the provincial level.
</P>
<P>
Since the launch of the campaign earlier this year, all
provincial procuratorates have publicized hotline numbers for
reporting violations of the law and discipline committed by
procuratorial staff.
</P>
<P>
In many places, the procurator-generals of local people's
procuratorates have set aside special days to receive and handle
reports from ordinary people. This practice has been well received.
</P>
</TEXT>
