<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Ruling Party Branch Secretary Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's ruling Freedom Party
branch secretary in Jaffna city S.A. Oswald was shot dead outside
his home Wednesday, according to reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
On the night of the incident, Oswald was about to close the
gates of his house around 8:30 p.m. when unidentified gunmen
opened fire on him, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Oswald had been living with his mother at his residence.
</P>
<P>
Police found his body lying on the road side in front of his
residence. Three bullets had pierced his scull.
</P>
<P>
Police investigation revealed that he had been threatened on
several occasions before the incident, said the reports, adding
that his killing is considered a political assassination.
</P>
<P>
Two incidents involving the killing of politicians occurred in
Jaffna city last month. The mayor of the city Sarojini Yogeswaran
was shot dead by a lone gunman on May 17 and army brigadier Larry
Wijeratne was killed by a Tamil rebel suicide bomber on May 14.
</P>
</TEXT>
