<HEADLINE> American Tourists to China Increase in Number </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- With the improvement of
Sino-American relationship, more and more Americans choose China as
their tourism destination, today's People's Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from the National Tourism Bureau show that
the number of American visitors had increased from 233,000 in 1990
to 616,000 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
China received 3,467,800 tourists in groups from the
United States during 1990-1997.
</P>
<P>
Some 200,000 Americans had visited China between January and
April this year, up two percent over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Their favorite tourism sites are Beijing, Shanghai, Xi'an and
Guilin. 
</P>
