<HEADLINE> Moya, Agassi, Chang Find Early Exit at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The men's star players kept falling
with Carlos Moya, Andre Agassi and Michael Chang all crashing out
of the on-going Wimbledon tennis championships on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On another rain-interupted day at Wimbledon, French Open
champion Carlos Moya of Spain seemed uncomfortable with the slick
grass. Winning the first set 6-4 easily, the fifth seed lost his
following three sets 4-6, 3-6, 4-6 to Hicham Arazi of Morocco.
</P>
<P>
13th seed Andre Agassi and fellow American fellow Micheal Chang
were also unable to produce expected top class tennis and lost
separately to Tommy Haas of Germay 6-4, 1-6, 6-7 (4-7), 4-6 and
Magns Gusfafsson of Sweden 2-6, 7-5, 2-6, 6-1, 2-6.
</P>
<P>
In the women's second round clashes, defending champion Martina
Hingis, third seed Jana Novotna and 7th seed Venus Williams
reached third round after beating their opponents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
