<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 00:00 GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, Yemen -- Five people were killed and 12 others wounded in riots
in Sanaa and other cities in the past few days, Yemeni Interior
Minister Hussein Moh'd Arab told a weekly published Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the "September 26th" weekly, the minister
said that two civilians were killed and six others, including four
policemen, were injured in Maareb, some 170 kilometers east of the
capital. (Yemen-Riot-Casualties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Negotiators from Israel and Palestine will meet in
the southeastern Greek island of Rhodes next month in an effort to
advance the peace procedures in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which will take place between July 1 and 5, will
be attended by Israel's labor and culture ministers, head of the
Palestinian negotiating team Faisal Husseini, European Union (EU)
envoy to the Middle East Miguel Angel Moratinos as well as
representatives from the EU, the United States and the European
Commission. (Israel-Palestine-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German leaders Thursday made it clear to visiting
