<HEADLINE> Romanian Government Creates "Romania's Star" Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government Thursday
decided to set up the "Steaua Romaniei" order (Romania's Star),
according to government sources.
</P>
<P>
It is the highest Romanian order for rewarding the exceptional
services, both civil and military, done on behalf of the Romanian
state and people.
</P>
<P>
The order can be granted to Romanian citizens for special acts
of great heroism.
</P>
<P>
The order can also be awarded to foreign citizens who greatly
contributed to the development of collaboration and friendship
relations with Romania or for exceptional deeds and services
brought to the Romanian state and people.
</P>
<P>
Order-conferring ceremony is to take place once a year for
Romanian winners, on December 1, the National Day of Romania.
</P>
</TEXT>
