<HEADLINE> U.S. Says Things Go Well in Hong Kong Since Transition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The United States said on
Thursday that things have gone well since the transition of Hong
Kong's sovereignty to China nearly one year ago and Hong Kong is a
"success story" in Asia's democracy.
</P>
<P>
"In general there has been a high degree of autonomy. Economic
commerce continues. The freedom of expression continues," Rubin
told a briefing at the Foreign Press Center.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the transition one year ago, many people in the West
were worried about the future of Hong Kong despite firm
commitments from the central Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
Rubin also praised the assembly election which took place last
month in the region, saying "clearly the voting was a strong
endorsement of democracy."
</P>
<P>
"So in that sense this Hong Kong is a success story for the
future of democracy in Asia and the importance of Hong Kong to the
U.S.-China relationship," said Rubin. 
