<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 543 Million U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved
Thursday a 543.2 million U.S. dollar assistance package to benefit
the state of Andhar Pradesh in India.
</P>
<P>
This poverty-focused project is a new type of state-level
lending operation in India to provide financial resources to
Andhra Pradesh for health, education, nutrition and rural
development targeted to the poorest areas.
</P>
<P>
With a population of some 73 million, Andhra Pradesh is one of
India's largest poor states with about 30 percent of its people
living below the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to address the needs in human
development such as primary education, primary health care
services, nutrition, irrigation rehabilitation and maintenance, as
well as rural development.
</P>
<P>
The package includes a 301.3 million dollar loan and a 241.9
million dollar equivalent interest-free credit from the
International Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's
concessional lending affiliate for developing countries. The total
project cost is some 830 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
