<HEADLINE> Death Toll From Stadium Stand Collapse Rises to 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from a stand
collapse Thursday at a sports complex in southern Russia has risen
to 22, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in Nalchik, capital city of the
Kabardino-Balkaria republic, as an opening ceremony for the
national freestyle wrestling championship was underway, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-three people were injured in the accident, three of them
in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, flags will fly at half mast in the republic to mourn
the victims, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin sent a cable, conveying his
condolences to Valery Kokov, the leader of the Kabardino-Balkaria
republic.
</P>
<P>
"I was shocked by the news about the tragedy in the capital of
your republic," Yeltsin said. "It was particularly hard that the
tragedy occurred during a festival -- the freestyle championship
among juniors."
</P>
<P>
The local government has set up a commission to investigate the
accident and promised financial compensation to the victims'
families and the injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
