<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0323 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA Members Urged to Meet Payment Obligation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing Vice Chairman of the
COMESA Council of Ministers Brig. Moses Ali Thursday urged all
members to meet their payment obligations to the organization in
time to avoid sanctions and keep the spirit of cooperation in the
bloc.
</P>
<P>
The vice chairman, who is also the Second Deputy Prime
Minister of Uganga, made the call when addressing the Council of
Ministers meeting of the Common Market for Eastern and Southern
Africa (COMESA) in Kinshasa, the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
He regretted the late payment of contributions which affects the
programs and activities of the COMESA Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Although they have not achieved much yet, they have been able to
realize modest success and most importantly they have managed to
keep together as an organization, Ali said.
</P>
<P>
He told the meeting that the building to house the COMESA
headquarters in Kampala has been secured with the restructuring and
reorganization of the secretariat nearly completed.
</P>
<P>
The COMESA court has also been established and trade between
member states of the organization has been increased, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
