<DOCNO> XIE19980626.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-25 18:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference on Arab Industrial Development Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The eighth conference on Arab
industrial development ended here Thursday with recommendations to
speed up the establishment of an Arab economic bloc that could
support the Arab countries under the new world order.
</P>
<P>
The conference, with the theme "the Arab industry under
international changes" and 800 participants from different
economic sectors in the Arab countries, discussed the status of
the Arab industry in particular and the Arab economies in general.
</P>
<P>
The conference recommended adoption of all possible means that
could improve the investment atmosphere to make the Arab region
more attractive to local and foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
The participants highlighted the necessity of supporting the
private sector through positive and effective participation in
charting industrial and economic policies of the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
