<HEADLINE> EU Urges Cambodia to Ensure Fair, Free Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) appealed to
the Cambodian government Thursday to ensure that the elections due
to be held next month are fair and free, saying successful
elections would mark an important step in the country's political
development.
</P>
<P>
Britain, the current EU president, said in a statement issued
on behalf of the 15-nation bloc that the EU was encouraged by the
success of a voter registration program and by the peaceful
campaigning of political parties throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
"The European Union urges the Cambodian Government to continue
to improve the situation by further promoting a political climate
conducive to free and fair elections," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed that EU would further encourage the
Cambodian government "to prevent any form of political
intimidation, violence, or malpractice in the election process and
to ensure that opposition leaders and their parties are given fair
access to the media."
</P>
<P>
"The European Union believes that successful elections would
mark an important step in Cambodia's political and economic
development," it added
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the EU has provided 11 million U.S.
dollars in assistance to create the conditions for fair and free
elections in Camdodia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
