<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Qualify with 1-0 Win over United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NANTES, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia qualified as the runners-up
of Group F after beating the United States 1-0 here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Only four minutes into the match, Savo Milosevic fired in a
powerful free-kick which was palmed away by American goal-keeper
Brad Friedel. Slobodan Komljenovc was just at the right place at
the moment and headed home to give the Yugoslav team the 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
The American team played a high-spirited game and threatened the
Yugoslav goal. Joe-Max-Moore and Brian McBride combined well and
surprised their opponents with blistering runs into the Yugoslavian
area.
</P>
<P>
But poor finishing failed them and they almost fell 2-0 behind
at the end of the first half when Milosevic ws tripped over the ball
in the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia strengthened their midfield and pushed players
forward, trying to get more goals to qualify for the last 16 as
group leaders.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Jugovic and Milosevic kept a constant pressure on the
American defence. Sinisa Mihajlovic curled a free-kick around the
wall, but Friedel scooped up the ball.
</P>
<P>
The Americans didn't give up and McBride nearly scored but his
low driving shot was collected by Yugoslav goal-keeper.
</P>
<P>
The 1-0 win is enough for the Yugoslav team to qualify, but as
the runners-up of the group. In a other Group F match, Germany beat
Iran 2-0 and advance into the last 16 as group winners due to better
goal difference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
